.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-PS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.25" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-ps \- Show tracked per\-service runtime state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose ps [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read tracked runtime state, log metadata, and scheduler state for each service in a submitted job. This is the compose\-style per\-service process view.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to inspect instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose ps \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose ps \-f compose.yaml \-\-job\-id 12345
hpc\-compose ps \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
